  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div xml:id="AN186.2-kilavi">
          <p type="edition">talaimakaṭkup pāṅkāyiṉāra kēṭpa illiṭaip parattai colliyatu.</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">What the other woman in the house said so that those close to HER would hear.</p>
        </div>
        <div xml:id="AN186.2">
      <lg type="edition">
        <l>vāṉam vēṇṭā vaṟaṉil vāḻkkai</l>
        <l>nōṉñāṇ viṉaiñar kōḷaṟin tīrkku</l>
        <l>mīṉmuti rilañcik kalitta tāmarai</l>
        <l>nīrmicai nivanta neṭuntā ḷakalilai</l>
        <l>yiruṅkayan tuḷaṅkak kāluṟu tōṟum</l>
        <l>peruṅkaḷiṟṟuc ceviyi ṉalaikku mūraṉo</l>
        <l>ṭeḻunta kēṇmaiyō peritē naṭpē</l>
        <l>koḻuṅkōl vēḻattup puṇaituṇai yākap</l>
        <l>puṉalāṭu kēṇmai yaṉaittē yavaṉē</l>
        <l>yoṇṭoṭi makaḷir maṇṭai pāḻpaṭa</l>
        <l>vīrntaṇ muḻavi ṉeṟikuṇil viti<supplied>r</supplied>ppat</l>
        <l>taṇṇaṟuñ cāntaṅ kamaḻun tōṇmaṇan</l>
        <l>tiṉṉum piṟaḷvayi ṉāṉē maṉaiyō</l>
        <l>ḷeṉṉoṭu pulakku meṉpa veṉvēṉ</l>
        <l>māri yampiṉ maḻaittōṟ paḻaiyaṉ</l>
        <l>kāviri vaippiṟ pē<supplied>e</supplied> ra<supplied>ṉ</supplied>ṉaveṉ</l>
        <l>ceṟivaḷai yuṭaittalō vilaḷē yuritaṉiṉ</l>
        <l>yāntaṉ pakaiyē mallēñ cērntōr</l>
        <l>tirunutal pacappa nīṅkuṅ</l>
        <l>koḻunaṉuñ cāluntaṉ ṉuṭaṉuṟai pakaiyē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
        <l>Great, ah, is the intimacy that has risen (7a-c)</l>
        <l rend="indent8">with the man from a village, (6d)</l>
        <l>where the wide leaves on the long stalks that have come up above the water (4)</l>
        <l>flap like the ears of a huge elephant bull, (6a-c)</l>
        <l>whenever they feel wind so that they sway in the big pond, (5)</l>
        <l>[the leaves] of the lotus that sprouted in the tank growing fish (3)</l>
        <l>that are dragged [out], knowing they’ve taken [the bait], by the workers with sturdy cords,</l>
        <l>[who have] a living without drought, not in need of the sky. (1f.)</l>
        <l rend="indent8">The friendship, (7d)</l>
        <l>it is like the intimacy of bathing [together] in the flood, (9a-c)</l>
        <l>with the help of a raft [in the form] of a big elephant bull. (8)</l>
        <l rend="indent8">He, (9d)</l>
        <l>he embraced [her] shoulders scented with cool sandal, (12)</l>
        <l>while the beating stick quivers, like on a moist cool drum, (11)</l>
        <l>so that the vessel of women with bright bracelets is ruined, (10)</l>
        <l>he still is at the side of another one. She in the house (13)</l>
        <l>is vexed with me, they say. (14a-c)</l>
        <l>As for breaking the tight bangles of me (17ab)</l>
        <l>who is like [the town] Pēer in the Kāviri region (16)</l>
        <l>of Paḻaiyaṉ with victorious spear [and] a cloud[-coloured] hide [shield]</l>
        <l>against the arrows [discharged like] a shower (14df.)</l>
        <l rend="indent8">not she. By rights (17cd)</l>
        <l>we have no quarrel with her. (18a-c)</l>
        <l>The quarrel that is hers concerns [her] husband, (20)</l>
        <l>who leaves those he joined, for [their] luminous foreheads to pale. (18df.)</l>
      </lg>
        </div>
